            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Melt 20g<span class=\"text-purple\"> [30g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[40g]</span> <strong>butter</strong> in a medium-sized pot over a medium heat</p><p>Once melted, add 20g<span class=\"text-purple\"> [30g] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[40g]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms</p><p>Gradually whisk in the <strong>creamy stock</strong>, a little at a time, and cook for 5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>white sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1676913903763-x200.jpg",
